in telecommunication, an automatic redial is a service feature that allows the user to dial, by depressing a single key or a few keys, the most recent telephone number dialed at that instrument. note: automatic redial is often associated with the telephone instrument, but may be provided by a pbx, or by the central office. synonym last number redial. contrast with automatic calling unit. often one must subscribe to a caller id for use of this function on a landline.